Israeli Stocks: Ituran Location, Visonic, Ormat Industries

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-21T10:51:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/israeli-stocks-ituran-location-visonic-ormat-industries.html
Israel’s TA-25 Index advanced 0.9
percent to 1,215.89 at 12:29 p.m. in  Tel Aviv .  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Atia Group Ltd. (ATIA)   gained the most since June 2,
increasing 12 percent to 0.249 shekel. The real-estate
development company has entered into an agreement in principle
to provide a 2.8 million-shekel ($820,000) loan for a 24 percent
stake in an unidentified Israeli gas explorer.  Ituran Location and Control Ltd. (ITRN)   headed for the
lowest close since November 2009, retreating 2.9 percent to
47.22 shekels. An Israeli court ordered the maker of systems
used to locate stolen vehicles to pay 78.7 million shekels in a
lawsuit.  Ormat Industries (ORMT)  Ltd rose the most since June 9,
adding 3.2 percent to 21.28 shekels. Ormat Technologies Inc.,
the U.S. unit of the developer of geothermal  power plants , has
won a project to develop and operate a geothermal power plant in
New Zealand.  Visonic Ltd. (VSC)   surged the most since at least April
2006, rallying 78 percent to 5.931 shekels. The Israeli maker of
security-alarm systems said it’s in talks to be acquired by Tyco
International Inc. based on a company value of $90 million to
$105 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
